285
00:15:42,100 --> 00:15:44,380
Merry Christmas!

286
00:15:44,980 --> 00:15:48,410
Friendship isn't about lots of words.

287
00:15:48,970 --> 00:15:51,830
I hear that a lot...

288
00:15:51,830 --> 00:15:53,100
What is it about, then?

289
00:15:53,880 --> 00:15:55,320
Give me a break...

290
00:15:55,320 --> 00:15:58,850
It's about... feelings?

291
00:15:59,030 --> 00:16:00,250
Feelings?

292
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:03,340
For instance, let's say you 
tell Kimari you like her.

293
00:16:03,340 --> 00:16:08,130
Kimari doesn't believe you, so she wants 
you to write it down on a piece of paper.

294
00:16:08,130 --> 00:16:10,890
You'd hate that, right? 
You'd feel like she didn't trust you.

295
00:16:10,890 --> 00:16:11,950
Well...

296
00:16:11,950 --> 00:16:14,230
Seconds, please!

297
00:16:15,330 --> 00:16:18,040
That's probably why she was crying.

298
00:16:20,050 --> 00:16:23,530
Yuzu, Kimari already sees you as a friend.

299
00:16:24,280 --> 00:16:26,930
But what makes us friends?

300
00:16:26,930 --> 00:16:29,170
How do you become friends?

301
00:16:29,170 --> 00:16:30,470
Well...

302
00:16:30,730 --> 00:16:33,970
There's probably no real way to define it.

303
00:16:35,050 --> 00:16:38,470
It's not like a parental 
or spousal relationship.

304
00:16:38,470 --> 00:16:40,110
It's more vague than that.

305
00:16:40,470 --> 00:16:43,200
No one's to blame if it fades.

306
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:44,190
Oh, no...

307
00:16:44,540 --> 00:16:46,520
That's the case for me, at least.

308
00:16:46,520 --> 00:16:48,670
But that's what lets it feel unrestrained.

309
00:16:48,670 --> 00:16:50,490
That's what lets us be together.

